      "content": "It's possible the symptoms might resolve on their own, but given the combination of tight chest and arm ache, the ER would be a better option to rule out any serious underlying issues. Taking an antacid might provide temporary relief, but if your symptoms worsen or persist, it's essential to have a medical professional assess you. If it's just indigestion, an antacid might help, but if you're still experiencing discomfort after 20 minutes, seek a more thorough evaluation at the ER.",
